    },
    {
      "type": "heading2",
      "text": "THE INTEGRATION MANTRA"
    },
    {
      "type": "cross_ref",
      "section": "Section 16",
      "note": "Web of Systems"
    },
    {
      "type": "prose",
      "text": "**Every worldbuilding element should do at least two of these:**"
    },
    {
      "type": "prose",
      "text": "1. Push characters together OR pull them apart (ideally both)"
    },
    {
      "type": "prose",
      "text": "2. Create opportunities for intimacy OR obstacles to overcome"
    },
    {
      "type": "prose",
      "text": "3. Force meaningful choices with real costs"
    },
    {
      "type": "prose",
      "text": "4. Have consistent rules the romance works within"
    },
    {
      "type": "prose",
      "text": "5. Matter to both the fantasy plot AND the relationship"
    },
    {
      "type": "prose",
      "text": "**If an element doesn't do at least two of these, cut it or strengthen it.**"
    },
    {
      "type": "divider"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading2",
      "text": "FINAL CHECKLIST BEFORE DRAFTING"
    },
    {
      "type": "checklist",
      "items": [
        "World at-a-glance complete",
        "Character details consistent",
        "Timeline established",
        "Magic rules clear (including what magic can't do)",
        "Bond mechanics defined, if applicable (consent, rejection, limits)",
        "Key locations defined",
        "Religion/belief system sketched (if relevant to romance)",
        "\"Why now?\" catalyst identified",
        "Obstacles identified with worldbuilding sources",
        "Power dynamics mapped",
        "Economic ledger understood",
        "Choice moments identified",
        "Climax integrates romance and fantasy",
        "Consistency rules clear",
        "Integration Score completed (Section 16)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "prose",
      "text": "**Ready to write.**"
    },
    {
      "type": "divider"
    },
    {
      "type": "prose",
      "text": "Keep these sheets accessible. Update as your story evolves."
    },
    {
      "type": "prose",
      "text": "Happy writing!"
    }
